# BITStu.ai V2 Roadmap

## Vision
BIT is an AI-native CRM and operations platform. Clients build Playbooks — 
DAG-structured workflows — that BIT executes using a multi-agent system 
grounded in a scoped Knowledge Base. Every action produces artifacts.

---

## Sprint 1 — Foundation (Week 1–2)
**Goal: Client + Admin dashboards live, auth, KB ingestion working**

### Dashboard (P0)
- [ ] Admin view: Playbook list, agent status, artifact log, flag controls
- [ ] Client view: Playbook creation UI, task DAG builder, artifact downloads
- [ ] Auth: role-based access (admin vs client vs BITStu-internal)

### Knowledge Base (P0)
- [ ] Ingest pipeline: raw data → structured KB entries
- [ ] Scope tagging: Public / External / Internal / Drafts
- [ ] KB read API for BIT to query

### Feature Flags (P0)
- [ ] Testing flag
- [ ] Prod flag
- [ ] Lead flag
- [ ] Flag management UI in admin dashboard

---

## Sprint 2 — Playbook Engine (Week 3–4)
**Goal: Clients can build and run Playbooks end-to-end**

- [ ] DAG task builder (sequential + branching tasks)
- [ ] Task executor with skill routing
- [ ] Skill registry (Skill #1…n pluggable)
- [ ] Effort levels per agent: Hard / Med / Easy
- [ ] Playbook completion → artifact generation
- [ ] Artifact storage + download

---

## Sprint 3 — Multi-Agent + Scale (Week 5–6)
**Goal: Parallel agents, agent monitoring, client onboarding**

- [ ] Agent pool: spawn Agent #1…n per playbook
- [ ] Agent status dashboard (live)
- [ ] Human documentation upload → KB ingestion flow
- [ ] Client self-onboarding
- [ ] Billing/plan gating on playbook runs

---

## Sprint 4 — Revenue + GTM (Week 7–8)
**Goal: First paid clients, VC-ready demo**

- [ ] Pricing tiers (SMB / Mid-market / Enterprise)
- [ ] Usage analytics dashboard
- [ ] Demo environment with preloaded playbooks
- [ ] Security audit + SOC2 prep
- [ ] Public-facing landing page + waitlist